Vice President Biden will kick off his "Road to Recovery" tour, traveling to communities across the country to highlight the impact of Recovery Act funds on job creation and infrastructure improvement. The tour will begin with stops in Carlisle, Pennsylvania and Overland Park, Kansas, where the Vice President will attend the groundbreaking ceremonies for transportation construction projects. He will then travel to Kalamazoo, Michigan for the groundbreaking ceremony of an interchange reconstruction project. The Vice President will also make remarks regarding communities affected by the auto industry at the Kalamazoo airport. These events will be open press.